# 1. Executive Summary

Bank fraud has become a major challenge for financial institutions due to the increasing number of digital transactions.

This project focuses on analyzing banking transaction data to identify fraudulent activities, understand fraud patterns, and generate meaningful business insights.

The project uses SQL for data analysis, Python for data exploration and cleaning, and Power BI for creating an interactive fraud monitoring dashboard.

The final outcome helps identify high-risk transactions, customers, and fraud trends that can support better fraud prevention strategies.

---

# 2. Business Problem

Banks handle millions of transactions daily. Manual monitoring of every transaction is difficult and time-consuming.

The organization needs a data-driven solution to:

* Detect fraudulent transactions
* Identify risky customers
* Analyze fraud patterns
* Monitor fraud trends
* Reduce financial losses

---

# 3. Project Objectives

The main objectives of this project are:

• Analyze transaction data and identify fraud cases

• Calculate total fraud transactions and fraud amount

• Identify customers involved in fraudulent activities

• Understand transaction behavior patterns

• Create an interactive dashboard for fraud monitoring

• Provide actionable business recommendations

---

# 4. Dataset Description

The dataset contains banking transaction information.

## Dataset Columns

| Column Name        | Description               |
| ------------------ | ------------------------- |
| transaction_id     | Unique transaction number |
| customer_id        | Customer identifier       |
| transaction_date   | Date of transaction       |
| transaction_amount | Amount transferred        |
| transaction_type   | Type of transaction       |
| location           | Transaction location      |
| payment_method     | Mode of payment           |
| is_fraud           | Fraud indicator           |

## Target Column

is_fraud:

0 → Normal Transaction

1 → Fraud Transaction

